FBIS4-8079 "dreeu069_i_94031" FBIS-EEU-94-069 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported Fighting, Situation Around Gorazde Reported `Bestial' Overnight Shelling AU1104084194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 11 Apr 94 AU1104084194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Fahrudin Becic report] [Text] There was no peace in Gorazde overnight. The Chetniks attacked the southern access to the town (?with infantry) throughout the night. Until midnight, they were attacking individual parts of the town and the [word indistinct] itself with howitzer and tank grenades. Afterward, they attacked [words indistinct] defense lines with mortars and the town [word indistinct] with snipers. This morning [words indistinct] somewhat intensified [words indistinct] that lasted here the entire night [words indistinct]. Shortly after 0800 [words indistinct], and infantry battles are under way in the area of the right bank access to the town. According to preliminary reports, the consequences of the bestial overnight shelling are seven [words indistinct] and [word indistinct] injured. Some of them [passage indistinct] in areas from which it is not possible to reach the town, is not known yet.
